		<description>Hi Phil, I&#039;m using codemirror for highlighting CoffeeScript in my site. My site is a custom Rails application inspired by Toto&#039;s idea:

http://codemirror.net/
https://github.com/cloudhead/toto

My articles are written in Markdown and code examples lie between &quot;@@@ language-identifier&quot;..&quot;@@@&quot; blocks.

Most are processed using CodeRay but for CoffeeScript I had to use client-side processing cause I couldn&#039;t find any Ruby highlighting library that understands CoffeeScript :(</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hi Phil, I&#8217;m using codemirror for highlighting CoffeeScript in my site. My site is a custom Rails application inspired by Toto&#8217;s idea:</p>
<p><a href="http://codemirror.net/" rel="nofollow">http://codemirror.net/</a><br />
<a href="https://github.com/cloudhead/toto" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/cloudhead/toto</a></p>
<p>My articles are written in Markdown and code examples lie between &#8220;@@@ language-identifier&#8221;..&#8221;@@@&#8221; blocks.</p>
<p>Most are processed using CodeRay but for CoffeeScript I had to use client-side processing cause I couldn&#8217;t find any Ruby highlighting library that understands CoffeeScript <img src='http://www.bigfastblog.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif' alt=':(' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
